<doc>
  <member name="CodecAPIEventData">
    <summary>
      <para>The <b>CodecAPIEventData</b> structure contains event data for the <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/DirectShow/ec-codecapi-event">EC_CODECAPI_EVENT</a> event. This event is sent by codecs that support the <see cref="ICodecAPI" /> interface.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>This structure may be followed by addition data, depending on the codec event. For more information, see <see cref="ICodecAPI.RegisterForEvent" />.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/DirectShow/directshow-structures">DirectShow Structures</seealso>
    <seealso cref="ICodecAPI.RegisterForEvent" />
  </member>
  <member name="CodecAPIEventData.guid">
    <summary>
      <para>A GUID that identifies the codec event.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="CodecAPIEventData.dataLength">
    <summary>
      <para>The length of the additional data that follows this structure, in bytes.
The value can be zero.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="CodecAPIEventData.reserved">
    <summary>
      <para>Reserved; do not use.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>